FBIS4-11702 "drnes062_r_94001" FBIS-NES-94-062 Daily Report 31 Mar 1994 SOUTH ASIA India Prime Minister Interviewed on Various Bilateral Relations Prime Minister Interviewed on Various Bilateral Relations BK3103091694 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0830 GMT 31 Mar 94 BK3103091694 Delhi All India Radio Network English BFN [Text] The prime minister has expressed the hope that enhanced cooperation between India and the United States will continue despite sharp differences in some areas of national importance. In an interview published in the latest issue of INDIA NEWS, Mr. Narasimha Rao described Indo-U.S. relations as multifaceted, complex, and replete with challenges and opportunities. He said U.S. is India's largest trading partner as well as the largest source of foreign direct investment. Referring to China, Mr. Rao said there has been steady improvement in Sino-Indian relations over the last few years. The uptrend in ties has facilitated attempts to resolve the difficult boundary question between the two countries.
